                        )(0.1 g), melamine (0.3 g) and ultra-pure water (20 mL) were added to beaker (50 mL) and stirred magneticall. The solution was transferred to a 50 mL high pressure reactor lined with teflon and placed in a 180℃vacuum oven for 12 h. After the reactor was cooled to room temperature, the solution was filtered by 0.22 μm drainage pinhole filter. Then, the filtrate was collected and dialyzed for 48 h using cellulose dialysis membranes (500 Da). The solution in dialysis bag was collected and dried for 12 h at 60℃. CDs were obtained by collecting solids and named as XM-CDs.
